{
  "stem": "1895.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Yes, we had a bar mitzvah rite in an-- in an apartment that was owned by a rabbi who lived in the apartment complex that we lived in.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he had created a room that was camouflaged with a wardrobe so that no one would know that there was an entry-- there's a room there.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was in this room that we went in to pray, because praying, of course, under the Germans was forbidden under the pain of death immediately, as soon as they entered.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And-- but my parents insisted, and we do go through this ritual.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we went into this room in the rabbi's house that was camouflaged with this wardrobe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when I was about to begin reciting the haftarah, Germans came in.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we heard on the outside the-- you know--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--rough shuffling with the screams-- Juden raus, Juden raus.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And everybody froze.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Germans actually came into the room, to the apartment where the rabbi lived, and they asked loudly, 'where are the males?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Where are the men?' Because they were-- they were-- at that point it was early in the war.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They would come down and raid the Jewish neighborhoods and grab males so that they would work for them and abuse them for whatever reasons they had.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they were on one of these raids that they came into that apartment.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, we were very close to having someone come in there, because they actually went into the-- opened the wardrobe doors from the other side, and one of them went into the wardrobe to look.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But somehow, he didn't find.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so eventually, they left.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I asked the people that were present there if I should continue reading the haftarah.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
